review: Love this yogurt.Can be tough to find.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2020
name: Donald P Morris
title: The BEST!
review: This is the best yogurt ever! Since I becamesensitive to cow milk this sheep milk yogurt is a blessing, allowing me to enjoy yogurt again.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2020
name: Hala S. Arafa
title: The Best Old Fashioned Creamy Yogurt
review: If you've ever lived on a farm & had fresh yogurt made in terra cotta bowls, this yogurt will remind you of that creamy, wholesome, fresh taste. Since I discovered this brand, I haven't been able to eat any other yogurt.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2020
name: J P Crouse
title: Great yogurt!
review: For those of us who can’t have cow yogurt, this is a great alternative.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2020
name: Jay Emm Gee
title: Perfect for non kosher lifestyle. No kosher tax stamp
review: Creamy, nutritious, pure & non kosher! No K or OU.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2021
name: Mpp
title: Very tangy (sour)
review: I wasn't prepared for the strength of the tanginess of this yogurt. I think it might be good for some recipes, but for what I was making, it was overwhelming.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2021
name: Lucy S.
title: Pricy, but good

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2021
name: Gwenevere
title: My favorite!
review: This is my favorite brand of yogurt. I'm sad that I rarely find it anywhere and I haven't seen the ginger since 2020. I hope this brand grows.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 19, 2021
name: Brian Davis
title: Very versatile

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2021
name: Mimi J
title: Thick and creamy.
review: I’d rate this 5 stars except flavor is no longer as sweet as it used to be.Tastes like too much rennet.It’s pricey but worth it to me since I cannot digest cow products and this is much thicker and creamier than goat yogurt.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on April 6, 2021
name: Lola SH
title: Sheep Milk is a wonderful natural superfood
review: Doesn't taste gamey, or petting-zoo-like. Tastes creamy, not sweet. Add honey and you've got yourself a treat, feels like you're eating icecream. The best of all? It's full of nutrients and easy on your stomach.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2021
name: JJ
title: Great yogurt
review: Love this yogurt. I'm lactose intolerant and this one causes no problems or discomfort.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2021
name: Vanessa East
title: Scrumptious
review: I love sheep milk products. They have a far superior flavor to cow milk products, in my opinion. Creamier and more delicate. I have problems with cow milk products that are more liquid than a soft spreadable cheese. This has never been the case with sheep milk. This particular yogurt was delicious and I will purchase again in the future.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2020
name: E Morris
title: Will buy again
review: Great tasting yogurt with a tang but no bitterness.

review: It seems they have changed the recipe and it does not have the same taste anymore
